00:07:39.630 --> 00:07:40.840
OMG...

00:07:40.840 --> 00:07:42.290
OMG?

00:07:42.290 --> 00:07:45.620
Hey, this is Beckenbesides, but do you
 know what "Floridya later" means?

00:07:45.620 --> 00:07:48.550
Can we start with what "Beckenbesides" means?!

00:07:48.900 --> 00:07:52.890
I dunno how I can talk about this 
stuff unless you know what I mean.

00:07:52.890 --> 00:07:54.360
I'm sorry.

00:07:55.430 --> 00:07:56.700
Oh well, then...

00:07:57.300 --> 00:07:59.740
First, I'm gonna teach you how 
all the cool people talk!

00:08:02.100 --> 00:08:04.280
All right, make sure to clean 
up for tomorrow, okay?

00:08:02.100 --> 00:08:04.740
So do you, like, know any 
kind of slang at all?

00:08:04.280 --> 00:08:05.900
Okay.

00:08:06.120 --> 00:08:07.160
Now, then...

00:08:08.380 --> 00:08:09.680
Uh, I've heard "XL" before...

00:08:09.680 --> 00:08:11.340
What does "XL" mean?!

00:08:11.340 --> 00:08:12.510
That didn't take long.

00:08:11.340 --> 00:08:12.860
It's not slang?!

00:08:23.320 --> 00:08:25.040
Did I say you could rest?

00:08:25.290 --> 00:08:26.740
Two more laps. Get moving.

00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:27.790
R-Right!

00:08:27.790 --> 00:08:28.590
Bourbon...

00:08:28.590 --> 00:08:29.320
Sir?

00:08:29.320 --> 00:08:32.150
The Satsukishou's 200 meters longer 
than the last race you ran.

00:08:32.150 --> 00:08:32.850
Yes, sir.

00:08:32.850 --> 00:08:34.890
Give me three more laps on the sloping track.

00:08:34.890 --> 00:08:36.800
As you wish, Master.

00:08:50.520 --> 00:08:52.770
It's a bit more crowded than usual, isn't it?

00:08:52.770 --> 00:08:54.570
It makes me kind of nervous!

00:08:54.570 --> 00:08:56.910
Okay, you want me to chase them off?

00:08:56.910 --> 00:08:59.220
Don't. Think of this as 
training to focus,

00:08:59.220 --> 00:09:01.490
no matter what kind of 
distractions there are.

00:09:01.490 --> 00:09:02.780
Are you going to be okay?

00:09:02.780 --> 00:09:06.660
I tend to do better when 
I'm being watched, anyway.

00:09:06.660 --> 00:09:08.130
It won't be a problem.

00:09:08.130 --> 00:09:10.670
One other thing—Teio and 
McQueen are going to be

00:09:10.670 --> 00:09:12.700
running different training 
regimens from now on.

00:09:13.590 --> 00:09:15.380
You two are competing at the Tennoushou.

00:09:15.380 --> 00:09:18.250
Until that's over, you probably 
shouldn't be too friendly.

00:09:18.250 --> 00:09:21.630
You'll want to work on your weaknesses, 
and come up with a winning strategy.

00:09:22.150 --> 00:09:23.650
I understand.

00:09:23.650 --> 00:09:25.270
You're right.

00:09:25.270 --> 00:09:28.270
Starting today, I'm not 
gonna talk to McQueen.

00:09:28.580 --> 00:09:30.400
A good idea.

00:09:32.590 --> 00:09:35.780
I guess you have to! 
Since this is a serious competition!

00:09:35.780 --> 00:09:37.930
So what's my training look like?

00:09:37.930 --> 00:09:39.590
You're gonna need these, Teio.

00:09:40.780 --> 00:09:42.660
Jogging shoes?

00:09:42.660 --> 00:09:45.000
And these are for McQueen.

