Strategy Meeting

00:09:58.160 --> 00:10:00.710
There's a chance that it's 
an exercise for boosting the

00:10:00.710 --> 00:10:02.380
flexibility of her knees and ankles.

00:10:02.380 --> 00:10:04.050
You really think so?

00:10:04.050 --> 00:10:06.350
The Teio Step is easy, anyway!

00:10:06.350 --> 00:10:07.010
Hup!

00:10:09.950 --> 00:10:12.110
All right, here I go!

00:10:12.110 --> 00:10:13.530
It's just like this...

00:10:18.880 --> 00:10:20.470
Everyone, what's all the noise...

00:10:21.680 --> 00:10:23.740
What happened to you?!

00:10:23.740 --> 00:10:25.770
Ow, ow, ow...

00:10:25.770 --> 00:10:28.790
I swear, we're gonna take Spica down...

00:10:38.730 --> 00:10:41.280
The Spring Tennoushou is 3,200 meters.

00:10:41.280 --> 00:10:43.800
You've never run a race that long before.

00:10:43.800 --> 00:10:46.770
So you need the endurance to 
handle the extra distance!

00:10:53.770 --> 00:10:56.400
Heavy

00:10:59.930 --> 00:11:00.780
So heavy!

00:11:01.080 --> 00:11:03.740
What the hell's this horseshoe made of? Lead?

00:11:03.740 --> 00:11:06.240
Those were the orders from Trainer-san.

00:11:06.580 --> 00:11:08.460
It's when you're feeling
worn out that you need

00:11:08.460 --> 00:11:10.250
to bring your knees up and 
take a big step forward.

00:11:10.250 --> 00:11:13.210
And to do that, you need hindquarters 
that can stand up to fatigue!

00:11:13.630 --> 00:11:17.210
Teio's greatest weapon is her explosive 
power during the final straight.

00:11:17.210 --> 00:11:20.030
I need to create hindquarters that 
are able to compete with hers.

00:11:23.320 --> 00:11:25.240
That's really something!

00:11:32.190 --> 00:11:33.600
What's up, McQueen?

00:11:35.770 --> 00:11:37.440
What? You need something?

00:11:36.020 --> 00:11:40.030
Umamusume

00:11:36.020 --> 00:11:40.030
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:39.580
Seriously, what are you looking at, huh?

00:11:40.440 --> 00:11:43.530
Today is the first race of the 
Triple Crown Classics, the Satsukishou.

00:11:43.530 --> 00:11:45.780
All eyes are focused on Mihono Bourbon.

00:11:46.150 --> 00:11:48.740
She will be entering the 
Satsukishou undefeated,

00:11:48.740 --> 00:11:50.780
just like last year's winner, Tokai Teio.

00:12:25.570 --> 00:12:27.510
I say we start with cheese tapioca.

00:12:27.510 --> 00:12:29.170
And then salmon roe tapioca.

00:12:29.170 --> 00:12:31.080
I want carrot tapioca!

00:12:32.100 --> 00:12:33.100
Teio-san!

00:12:33.100 --> 00:12:34.120
Okay...

00:12:34.120 --> 00:12:36.180
Would you like to join us, Teio-san?

00:12:36.180 --> 00:12:37.130
Yeah, let's hang out.

00:12:37.130 --> 00:12:39.630
Can't. Not dressed for it.

00:12:40.920 --> 00:12:43.460
Well, the Tennoushou is next week.

00:12:45.350 --> 00:12:46.510
McQueen-san...

00:12:47.010 --> 00:12:49.390
McQueen, you want in on this tapi...o...ca?

00:12:51.850 --> 00:12:53.830
Makes sense.

00:12:53.830 --> 00:12:55.820
I'm not going out anymore.

00:12:56.310 --> 00:12:59.340
Two of our teammates are giving 
up their days off to train.

00:12:59.340 --> 00:13:01.440
I can't just sip on bubble tea 
like nothing's going on.

00:13:02.550 --> 00:13:03.650
Good point.

00:13:04.340 --> 00:13:07.490
Yeah. Let's help them with their training!

00:13:11.910 --> 00:13:16.080
Today's star competitor is going to be 
running in the Satsukishou undefeated.

00:13:16.080 --> 00:13:18.140
And here's Mihono Bourbon!

00:13:40.650 --> 00:13:42.180
This is brutal!

00:13:42.180 --> 00:13:44.580
You've been running up this hill every day?!

00:13:44.580 --> 00:13:46.900
Sure have! Trainer's orders.

00:13:46.900 --> 00:13:50.600
You've never run a 3,200 meter 
race before, have you, Vodka?

00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:52.900
Hell no! You haven't either, right, Scarlet?

00:13:52.900 --> 00:13:53.950
Of course not!

00:13:53.950 --> 00:13:56.750
I have no idea how you'd pace yourself!

00:13:56.750 --> 00:14:00.000
But McQueen won the Tennoushou last year.

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:03.640
And the Hanshin Daishoten, 
which is 3,000 meters.

00:14:06.710 --> 00:14:09.300
H-Hey, wait up!

00:14:12.160 --> 00:14:14.840
Seriously, don't land on me!

00:14:14.840 --> 00:14:17.360
If you land on me with those horseshoes,
you'll gouge my back out!

00:14:17.360 --> 00:14:18.470
It's fine.

00:14:18.470 --> 00:14:19.100
How, exactly?!

00:14:19.100 --> 00:14:20.660
Here we go.

00:14:20.660 --> 00:14:22.140
Ready, and...

00:14:24.610 --> 00:14:28.650
Wow! I'm amazed you can jump 
in such heavy horseshoes!

00:14:28.650 --> 00:14:30.610
This is terrifying! 
Do you really need me?!

00:14:30.900 --> 00:14:33.790
Teio has never lost.

00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:36.540
If it helps me defeat an undefeated horse girl,

00:14:36.540 --> 00:14:37.500
then this is a small price.

00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:39.250
Hey, the donut truck!

00:14:41.710 --> 00:14:42.390
Oh, my.

00:14:42.390 --> 00:14:44.590
Are you okay, Gold Ship-san?!

00:14:44.880 --> 00:14:46.170
Ready, and...

00:14:46.170 --> 00:14:48.630
Machikane Tannhäuser!

00:14:57.370 --> 00:14:59.110
Her name's kinda long, huh?

00:14:59.110 --> 00:15:00.670
Perhaps just "Tannhäuser."

00:15:00.670 --> 00:15:02.270
No! What about "Machitan"?

00:15:02.270 --> 00:15:04.140
We could just call her "Macchy."

00:15:04.140 --> 00:15:05.700
Does it matter?

00:15:04.380 --> 00:15:06.780
Nah, I like mine, it sounds 
like a world champ!

00:15:15.010 --> 00:15:18.980
Keep up... Keep up...
Keep up... Keep up...

00:15:23.040 --> 00:15:26.160
Mihono Bourbon's strength is 
thought to be short distances,

00:15:26.160 --> 00:15:29.050
but going into this race, she's been 
undertaking intensive slope training.

00:15:29.270 --> 00:15:33.490
Her trainer Kuronuma's philosophy 
is that speed is a natural gift,

00:15:33.490 --> 00:15:35.680
while stamina can be compensated 
for with training.

00:15:36.120 --> 00:15:37.310
Is that so?

00:15:37.310 --> 00:15:40.680
It sounds like she'll be heading into the 
Classics ready to tear up those hills!

00:15:40.940 --> 00:15:44.940
Mihono Bourbon, huh? Seems like stronger 
and stronger horse girls keep showing up.

00:15:44.940 --> 00:15:47.220
Will she be able to follow in the 
footsteps of Tokai Teio

00:15:47.220 --> 00:15:49.720
and take the Satsukishou while undefeated?

00:15:49.720 --> 00:15:51.700
They're talking about you, Teio!

00:15:51.950 --> 00:15:55.450
I was really sure that I was 
gonna win the Satsukishou!

00:15:55.450 --> 00:15:57.580
What about this time, then?

00:15:57.820 --> 00:15:58.780
This time?

00:15:59.580 --> 00:16:03.460
The gate is open and the race has begun. 
Mihono Bourbon's off to a good start.

00:16:03.780 --> 00:16:05.960
Huh, that's a nice start.

00:16:05.960 --> 00:16:09.490
Mihono Bourbon has never lost before, either.

00:16:09.490 --> 00:16:11.590
She's just like Teio-san!

00:16:11.970 --> 00:16:15.090
I wonder if that adds to the pressure.

00:16:15.670 --> 00:16:19.100
Mihono Bourbon is out in front 
of 16 other horse girls!

00:16:19.370 --> 00:16:22.560
Will she remain in first place all the 
way through to the end of the race?

00:16:24.640 --> 00:16:27.110
I didn't know Bourbon-chan was this fast!

00:16:29.360 --> 00:16:31.360
There's definitely some pressure.

00:16:31.360 --> 00:16:33.840
I didn't know you ever felt pressure.

00:16:33.840 --> 00:16:35.090
It's surprising.

00:16:35.090 --> 00:16:39.360
But I think a race without 
 pressure wouldn't be any fun.

00:16:39.360 --> 00:16:44.370
I think I feel more pressure about the 
Tennoushou than I did about the Derby.

00:16:44.370 --> 00:16:47.880
Which is why I'm looking 
forward to it more, too!

00:16:52.550 --> 00:16:58.160
You already won last time, McQueen-san, 
so I doubt you feel much pressure at all.

00:16:58.160 --> 00:17:01.570
Teio wasn't running in 
the Tennoushou when I won.

00:17:01.890 --> 00:17:07.350
She is without a doubt a better racer 
than any other that I've faced before.

00:17:07.350 --> 00:17:09.840
Which definitely is a source of pressure,

00:17:09.840 --> 00:17:12.340
but getting melodramatic 
about it serves no purpose.

00:17:13.390 --> 00:17:15.200
You're pretty tough, McQueen.

00:17:15.200 --> 00:17:16.110
Really!

00:17:16.110 --> 00:17:17.280
Less than 200 meters to go!

00:17:17.280 --> 00:17:18.900
The gap has grown from two lengths to three!

00:17:18.900 --> 00:17:20.670
Mihono Bourbon is in the lead!

00:17:20.670 --> 00:17:22.960
She is looking seriously, incredibly strong!

00:17:22.960 --> 00:17:26.710
Mihono Bourbon manages to outrun 
them all and cross the goal!

00:17:26.710 --> 00:17:29.860
She takes the Satsukishou while undefeated!

00:17:37.220 --> 00:17:39.790
Machikane Tannhäuser...

00:17:39.790 --> 00:17:41.220
What happened to the other names?

00:17:45.230 --> 00:17:47.640
Damn, Mihono Bourbon!

00:17:49.020 --> 00:17:51.530
You can compensate for 
stamina with training...

00:17:53.610 --> 00:17:57.080
Okay, break's over! One more time!

00:17:57.080 --> 00:17:58.700
You're not done yet?!

00:17:58.700 --> 00:18:00.410
H-Hang on!

00:18:00.410 --> 00:18:03.870
Now, Gold Ship, 
place your hands on your knees.

00:18:04.190 --> 00:18:07.620
You sure about this? 
It's even higher than before!

00:18:07.620 --> 00:18:10.350
This would be no problem 
at all with Teio's knees.

00:18:10.350 --> 00:18:11.770
One hundred reps, let's begin.

00:18:14.020 --> 00:18:15.590
Teio...

00:18:15.590 --> 00:18:17.990
Not a damn word, Spe! I swear!

00:18:17.990 --> 00:18:19.630
You'll distract McQueen!

00:18:20.090 --> 00:18:21.670
She's not even there?!

00:18:21.670 --> 00:18:22.510
You two!

00:18:22.510 --> 00:18:24.100
Would you like some donuts?!

00:18:25.660 --> 00:18:26.110
Oh, my.

00:18:26.110 --> 00:18:28.310
Are you okay, Gold Ship-san?!

00:18:26.640 --> 00:18:31.950
Are you aiming for the undefeated Triple Crown
 that Tokai Teio was unable to achieve?

00:18:31.950 --> 00:18:35.190
Yes. Those are Master's orders, 
and I will carry them out.

00:18:35.190 --> 00:18:36.940
Now, one more time!

00:18:38.510 --> 00:18:44.080
Tennoushou
(Spring)

00:18:38.510 --> 00:18:44.080
{\an9}Press
Conference

00:18:42.110 --> 00:18:44.700
This weekend is the long-awaited 
Spring Tennoushou.

00:18:44.700 --> 00:18:48.710
First, Tokai Teio-san, this is going 
to be the first TM race ever,

00:18:48.710 --> 00:18:50.190
and all of Japan is excited.

00:18:50.190 --> 00:18:52.710
A TM race? Not an MT?

00:18:50.460 --> 00:18:52.290
Do you have any comments 
heading into the race?

00:18:53.250 --> 00:18:54.840
Are they favoring Teio?

00:18:54.840 --> 00:18:57.400
Well, I've never lost before!

00:18:57.400 --> 00:18:59.970
And that's not gonna change, 
even against McQueen!

00:19:01.110 --> 00:19:04.500
Mejiro McQueen-san, you won the 
Spring Tennoushou last year.

00:19:04.500 --> 00:19:06.100
What are your chances this year?

00:19:06.100 --> 00:19:07.580
More than sufficient.

00:19:07.580 --> 00:19:09.100
I have no intention of losing to Teio.

00:19:10.100 --> 00:19:12.160
I'm ready to run to the ends of the earth!

00:19:12.160 --> 00:19:14.980
Then I'll simply run to the heavens!

00:19:15.610 --> 00:19:17.560
I'm definitely gonna win!

00:19:15.610 --> 00:19:17.560
I shall be the winner!

00:19:17.560 --> 00:19:19.360
I assure you all, I'll win!

00:19:17.560 --> 00:19:20.750
I'm telling you, it's me!

00:19:19.360 --> 00:19:20.750
Just watch!

00:19:25.870 --> 00:19:28.620
T VS M: RACE OF THE MILLENNIUM
IT'S FINALLY HAPPENING!
THE UNDEFEATED HORSE GIRL TOKAI TEIO VS MEJIRO MCQUEEN IN HER ATTEMPT FOR A CONSECUTIVE WIN!

00:19:25.870 --> 00:19:29.610
Are we looking at the first ever 
undefeated winner of the Tennoushou?

00:19:29.610 --> 00:19:32.320
And does the crowd favor Tokai Teio?

