00:19:34.280 --> 00:19:37.630
The match of the millennium 
is drawing ever closer!

00:19:37.630 --> 00:19:39.540
Tennoushou (Spring)

00:19:37.630 --> 00:19:39.540
The Undefeated
 Tokai Teio

00:19:37.630 --> 00:19:39.540
Reigning Champ
Mejiro McQueen

00:19:48.560 --> 00:19:49.100
Wha?!

00:19:49.100 --> 00:19:50.930
THE UNDEFEATED HORSE GIRL
TOKAI TEIO

00:19:49.100 --> 00:19:51.100
Uma Sports
<font size="40">TOKAI TEIO</font>

00:19:49.100 --> 00:19:51.100
THE HORSE GIRL WHO
 WOULD BE THE
UNDEFEATED
 TENNOUSHOU WINNER

00:19:49.470 --> 00:19:51.100
RUNNING TO THE ENDS OF THE EARTH!!!

00:20:06.570 --> 00:20:07.910
Good work, Teio.

00:20:09.330 --> 00:20:10.790
Prez!

00:20:15.290 --> 00:20:17.880
I see. Your trainer's orders, then?

00:20:17.880 --> 00:20:22.300
I've never been in a race longer 
than 2,400 meters, after all.

00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:25.380
It's true. The distance is 
an advantage for McQueen.

00:20:25.380 --> 00:20:27.410
Yeah. But...

00:20:27.410 --> 00:20:30.520
I've just never been in a long race before.

00:20:30.890 --> 00:20:33.480
We don't know if I'm any good at it or not.

00:20:34.950 --> 00:20:35.620
True.

00:20:36.100 --> 00:20:39.760
The TV and papers seem to 
think I've got the edge,

00:20:40.330 --> 00:20:42.650
but I'm thinking of myself as 
the challenger in this race.

00:20:43.570 --> 00:20:46.110
Mihono Bourbon proved it, after all.

00:20:46.110 --> 00:20:49.250
The limits of stamina can be 
overcome through training!

00:20:49.800 --> 00:20:50.990
That's the spirit.

00:20:50.990 --> 00:20:54.570
I wasn't able to become an undefeated 
Triple Crown horse girl.

00:20:54.570 --> 00:20:57.210
But I can keep being undefeated!

00:20:57.570 --> 00:21:00.570
That's right. Keep rising 
to the challenge, Teio!

00:21:00.960 --> 00:21:01.890
Yeah!

00:21:01.890 --> 00:21:05.850
I know! If I win the Tennoushou, 
come with me to karaoke again!

00:21:05.850 --> 00:21:06.860
Fair enough.

00:21:12.350 --> 00:21:17.390
Excuse me... Grandmother, 
have you seen the news today?

00:21:17.390 --> 00:21:18.230
I have.

00:21:18.230 --> 00:21:21.230
In print and on television, 
it's Teio this, Teio that...

00:21:21.230 --> 00:21:24.720
I'm honestly shocked at the 
public's impression of the race.

00:21:24.720 --> 00:21:28.360
I was shocked after seeing you at 
the press conference, personally.

00:21:29.770 --> 00:21:33.630
I read you the tale of the tortoise 
and the hare as a child, didn't I?

00:21:33.630 --> 00:21:35.020
Y-You did.

00:21:35.020 --> 00:21:37.710
Do you understand how the tortoise won?

00:21:39.610 --> 00:21:42.220
The rabbit was looking at the tortoise.

00:21:42.220 --> 00:21:45.130
But the tortoise was looking at the goal.

00:21:46.110 --> 00:21:48.480
Do you understand what I'm trying to say?

00:21:53.420 --> 00:21:55.660
Having a rival is important.

00:21:56.440 --> 00:22:00.520
But there should be something 
more important than that.

00:22:02.390 --> 00:22:07.140
It's all right, Grandmother. I will not lose!

00:22:26.960 --> 00:22:28.060
I can do this!

00:22:28.060 --> 00:22:29.050
You can do this!

00:22:29.050 --> 00:22:30.350
I've got treats!

00:22:31.530 --> 00:22:32.020
Oh, my.

00:22:32.020 --> 00:22:34.150
Are you okay, Gold Ship-san?!

00:22:34.150 --> 00:22:37.020
The Spring Tennoushou is about to begin!

